
GBIOS release notes 05-07-92

1.0 - Introduction

The Gryphon BIOS will provide a set of services for using some of the
unique devices in the Gryphon system.  GBIOS (GBIOS.COM) is a TSR
program that emulates many of the Gryphon BIOS services.

GBIOS implements the functions documented in section 4 of the Gryphon
BIOS API specification.  This TSR must be executed before using any of
these funcitons.  GBIOS hooks INT 15h to install the Gryphon BIOS
services.  Note that if you have a previous version of GBIOS it may
have been named GBIOS.EXE instead of GBIOS.COM.

GBIOS works with the various development system adapter boards which
emulate some of the subsystems of the Gryphon system.  These include
the memory card adapter board, hand controller adapter board, and audio
adapter board.

GBIOS.COM can accept the following command line parameters.  Command
line parsing is very primitive so be sure to follow these formats
precisely.  All caps, no spaces between slashes and equals.

	/HI=x	where x is the IRQ assigned to the hand controller card

	/WI=x	where x is the IRQ assigned to the wave audio card

	/WD=x	where x indicates which DMA channel the wave audio card
		uses.  x=1 for DMA channel 5, x=2 for DMA channel 6,
		and x=3 for DMA channel 7.  In other words, x+4 is the
		DMA channel you want to use.

These defaults are used if the corresponding command line parameter is
missing.

	hand controller on IRQ 3

	wave audio on IRQ 7 and DMA 7

