The following sections contain notes on the various services provided
by GBIOS.  Refer to the Gryphon BIOS API specification February 27,
1992 for more information.

2.0 - System services (INT15h/AX=7100h)

All the functions are implemented with the following limitations.

Get Equipment List (INT15h/AX=7100h/BH=1) will indicate a keyboard is 
installed only if a 101-key keyboard is installed.  It will indicate a 
mouse is installed only if a mouse driver (MOUSE.COM) is installed.  If 
you loading a mouse driver, MOUSE.COM should be executed before 
GBIOS.COM.

The information returned by Get System Information
(INT15h/AX=7100h/BH=3) may change but the general format of the
information is correct.

3.0 - Hand controller services (INT15h/AX=7101h)

All functions are implemented.

Get Hand Controller Information (INT15h/AX=7101h/BH=0), which can be
used to reset the hand controller system, will NOT clear the callback
address as documented in the 02/27/92 API spec.  This is a spec change.

4.0 - Waveform output services.

All functions are implemented.

5.0 - Waveform input services.

All functions are implemented.

Failures are known to occur when recording.  The frequency of the
failures will vary from system to system.

6.0 - Synthesizer services

None, nothing, zilcho, nill, null, goose egg, no functions are
implemented.  More information and code updates will be provided as it
becomes available.

7.0 - Mixer services

All functions are implemented.

